history.content: Don't think you should try picking up too many commitments with CS 162; that is a beast of a class and will end up taking a lot of your time so do account for that.

children.subject:
I would recommend 161 over 194 for applications focused knowledge, but 194 is a more consistent workload.

I think 162 and 170 is already a full workload and I would avoid adding more. You can always drop classes later, though.

history.content: So I'm planning on graduating by the end of Spring 2020, and my current schedule for Fall is CS 162, CS 170, and CS 161 or CS 194, still deciding between those. I was also thinking of maybe adding on CS 186 for that semester, but given that I am going to be spending time applying and recruiting, as well as making a last ditch effort to get into some of the clubs like the ML club, would it be feasible to take 186 as well?
history.subject: Schedule Advice
